objects.name: NCSC
objects.description: The UK National Cyber Security Centre (NCSC) is the primary author and publisher of this report. NCSC conducted the analysis, authored the YARA rules, and provided recommendations and findings.

objects.name: Dropper for keylogger DLL
objects.description: Malicious dropper executable that drops the keylogger DLL as part of the Wishful Woodchuck malware campaign.
objects.pattern: [file:name = 'msvrt.exe' AND file:parent_directory_ref.path LIKE 'Unknown (dropped to execution directory)']

objects.name: Keylogger DLL (x86)
objects.description: Malicious DLL dropped by msvrt.exe, implements keylogging functionality for Wishful Woodchuck.
objects.pattern: [file:name = 'lMM32.dll' AND file:parent_directory_ref.path LIKE 'Unknown (dropped to execution directory)']

objects.name: Keylogger DLL (x86)
objects.description: Malicious DLL used by Wishful Woodchuck for keylogging on x86 systems.
objects.pattern: [file:name = 'hlpapi.dll' AND file:parent_directory_ref.path LIKE 'Unknown (dropped to execution directory)']

objects.name: Keylogger DLL (x64)
objects.description: Malicious executable for x64 systems, part of Wishful Woodchuck keylogger variants.
objects.pattern: [file:name = 'Manualmap_injector.exe' AND file:parent_directory_ref.path LIKE 'Unknown (dropped to execution directory)']

objects.name: Keylogger log file
objects.description: Log file created by Wishful Woodchuck keylogger DLL, contains encoded keystroke logs.
objects.pattern: [file:name = 'msimm.dat' AND file:parent_directory_ref.path LIKE 'Same directory as DLL/executable']

objects.name: Keylogger DLL (x64)
objects.description: Malicious DLL for x64 architecture, part of Wishful Woodchuck keylogger variants.
objects.pattern: [file:name = 'lMM64.dll' AND file:parent_directory_ref.path LIKE 'Unknown (dropped to execution directory)']

objects.name: Keylogger DLL (x64, VMProtected)
objects.description: VMProtected variant of the Wishful Woodchuck keylogger for x64 systems.
objects.pattern: [file:name = 'Manualmap_injector.vmp.exe' AND file:parent_directory_ref.path LIKE 'Unknown (dropped to execution directory)']

objects.name: Keylogger executable (x86)
objects.description: Malicious executable variant of Wishful Woodchuck keylogger for x86 systems.
objects.pattern: [file:name = 'WEXTRACT.EXE' AND file:parent_directory_ref.path LIKE 'Unknown (dropped to execution directory)']

objects.name: wishful woodchuck
objects.description: Wishful Woodchuck is a non-persistent Windows keylogger that logs keystrokes to a file on disk. It uses Windows API calls to hook the keyboard and writes the log file in an XOR-encoded format with a multi-byte key embedded in the binary. The malware contains no persistence or communications functionality and employs several defense evasion techniques, including XOR obfuscation of function names and strings, dynamic API resolution, and masquerading as legitimate Windows binaries. Multiple variants exist for both x86 and x64 architectures, delivered as executables or DLLs.

objects.name: Turla
objects.description: Turla is a threat group suspected to be the author of Wishful Woodchuck. The group is known for using XOR 0x55 obfuscation of function names and the TVer versioning string in their malware. Their motivations are espionage and stealth, and they employ defense evasion techniques such as string obfuscation and masquerading.

objects.name: wishfulwoodchuck_hardcoded_xorkey
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern:
rule wishfulwoodchuck_hardcoded_xorkey
{
    meta:
        author = "NCSC"
        description = "Finds binaries containing the hardcoded XOR key
from the keylogger binaries"

    strings:
        $xorkey = {0A 19 59 2D 6C 59 6F FA 8B 6F 9B FF 37 9B BD 7B 59 4B
7B DD 0F 64 91 C7 D6 9C 6F 7B 9C 01 9C 91 79 C7 C8 C9 DF E1 FA FF 04 08
59 E6 64 6D 37 9B 38 81 2D 81 65 7D 66 9A}

    condition:

uint16(0) == 0x5A4D and
uint32(uint32(0x3c)) == 0x00004550 and
all of them

}

objects.name: wishfulwoodchuck_file_description
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern:
rule wishfulwoodchuck_file_description
{
    meta:
        author = "NCSC"
        description = "Unique file description"

strings:

$description = "Multi-User Windows IMM32 API CIient DLL" wide

condition:

uint16(0) == 0x5A4D and
uint32(uint32(0x3c)) == 0x00004550 and
all of them

}

objects.name: wishfulwoodchuck_logfile_encodedheader
objects.description: YARA rule to detect related activity.
objects.pattern:
rule wishfulwoodchuck_logfile_encodedheader
{
    meta:
        author = "NCSC"
        description = "Encoded log file header"

    strings:
        $header = {41 19 0A 2D 20 59 5F FA 81 6F CF FF 61 9B D8 7B 2B 4B
46}
    condition:
        all of them
}
